\[r - r \cos \theta = 1.\]Then $r = 1 + r \cos \theta = x + 1,$ so
\[r^2 = (x + 1)^2 = x^2 + 2x + 1.\]Hence, $x^2 + y^2 = x^2 + 2x + 1,$ so
\[y^2 = 2x + 1.\]This represents the graph of a parabola, so the answer is $\boxed{\text{(C)}}.$

